#: ../../docs/classes/class_backbuffercopy.rst:14
msgid ""
"Copies a region of the screen (or the whole screen) to a buffer so it can"
" be accessed in your shader scripts through the ``texture(SCREEN_TEXTURE,"
" ...)`` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_backbuffercopy.rst:17
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_backbuffercopy.rst:19
msgid ""
"Node for back-buffering the currently-displayed screen. The region "
"defined in the BackBufferCopy node is bufferized with the content of the "
"screen it covers, or the entire screen according to the copy mode set. "
"Use the ``texture(SCREEN_TEXTURE, ...)`` function in your shader scripts "
"to access the buffer."
msgstr ""

